### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

Computed is a function to derive state synchronously. Resource expresses derived state from a synchronous reactive primitive. Itâ€™d be ideal to have an API to derive state from resource. Currently, it is possible to derive the value of a resource with another computed, but that loses al the state from the original async operation.

### Proposed solution

In the resource API, let the params support returning dependent resource instances. Once they are resolved, the values will be passed to the loader. The status of the derived resource would contemplate the async state of parent resources.

```ts
const userIdResource = resource(â€¦);

const userResource = resource({
  // userIdResource is an instance of a resource
  params: {id: userIdResource},
  loader: ({params, abortSignal}): Promise<User> => {
    return fetch(`users/${params.id}`, {signal: abortSignal});
  },
});

```

### Alternatives considered

Deriving just the value, but that is not ergonomic.

